<SUBJECT>D -- CONNECTIONS- Telecommunication Equipments and Services, Support Services, and Solutions
<SOLNBR>Reference-Number-9TE-PM-02-0001
<RESPDATE>020502
<ARCHDATE>12302002
<CONTACT>Paul Martin, Contract Specialist, Phone (510) 637-3884, Fax (510) 637-3883, Email paul.martin@gsa.gov - Paul Martin, Contract Specialist, Phone (510) 637-3884, Fax (510) 637-3883, Email paul.martin@gsa.gov
<DESC>The General Services Administration, Federal Technology Service, Regional Services Program hereby issues a Request for Proposal (RFP) for a Government-wide agency contract (GWAC) to provide Federal customers with a broad range of telecommunications equipment and services.  The Solicitation Number 9TE-PM-02-0001 for CONNECTIONS provides equipment, labor, and turnkey solutions to meet a variety of telecommunications infrastructure needs worldwide.  This will be Full and Open Multiple Award Indefinite Delivery Indefinite Quality contract vehicle with a base of three years and five one-year renewal options.  The technical scope has been divided into three categories:  (1) Equipment and Services ? commercial off-the-shelf telecommunications equipment and services; (2) Support Services ? defines requirements, assess alternatives, design solutions, and install, operate, upgrade, maintain, and de-install equipment and services; (3)  Solutions ? commercially available products and services or customized approaches.  The Government anticipates awarding CONNECTIONS contracts in a tiered phased approach.  There are staggered Prposal Due Dates for National, Global and States awards as referenced in Section L.15 of the solicitation and/or any revisions noted in the amendments. The maximum ceiling of the GWAC is $35 Billion.  The Government will not provide hardcopy/paper solicitations, however, the Request for Proposals is available by downloading from the GSA?s website at answer.gsa.gov/CONNECTIONS.  Evaluation will be competitive and based on best value, with non-priced factors are significantly more important than price.  The Contracting Officer will receive all questions concerning this procurement via the GSA email address CONNECTIONS@gsa.gov identified by the Solicitation Number 9TE-PM-02-0001.  Phone calls to the Contracting Officer are discouraged.
